Trim the ends off a few stalks of celery and slice them into small pieces. Wash and dry the leaves from one head of broccoli. Trim the bottoms off of the broccoli stalks and cut them into small pieces. Wash and dry a handful of asparagus spears.

Prepare the grilled meats: Cut four pounds of pork shoulder into bite-sized pieces. Place the pork in a baking dish and season with salt, pepper, and paprika. Place in the oven to cook for an hour. Meanwhile, remove the skin from four chicken breasts and pat them dry with paper towels. Season with salt, pepper, and paprika and place on a baking sheet in the oven to cook for half an hour.

Add one cup of tomato sauce and cook for another five minutes until heated through. Add one cup of barbecue sauce, one cup of ketchup, one cup of mustard, one tablespoon each of Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, honey, molasses, brown sugar, chili powder, paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper.
